0%", "bbox": [885.8, 1036.5, 934.4, 1057.3]}, {"text": "100%", "bbox": [974.4, 1036.5, 1023.0, 1057.3]}, {"text": "100%", "bbox": [1062.9, 1036.5, 1111.6, 1057.3]}, {"text": "Sales increased 40%, 28%, and 29% in 2010, 2009, and 2008. Changes in currency exchange rates", "bbox": [185.5, 1099.0, 1008.2, 1119.9]}, {"text": "positively (negatively) affected net sales by $(86) million, $(182) million, and $127 million for 2010, 2009, and", "bbox": [143.8, 1124.0, 1077.6, 1144.9]}, {"text": "2008. For a discussion of the effect on sales growth of exchange rates, see “Effect of Exchange Rates” below.", "bbox": [143.8, 1149.0, 1060.2, 1169.9]}, {"text": "The North America sales growth rate was 46%, 25%, and 26% in 2010, 2009, and 2008. The sales growth in", "bbox": [185.5, 1199.1, 1091.6, 1219.9]}, {"text": "each year primarily reflects increased unit sales, a larger base of sales in faster growing categories such as", "bbox": [143.8, 1224.1, 1029.0, 1244.9]}, {"text": "electronics and other general merchandise, and, in 2010, our adoption of the new accounting standard update", "bbox": [143.8, 1249.1, 1052.7, 1269.9]}, {"text": "(“ASU”) 2009-13 (see Item 8 of Part II, “Financial Statements and Supplementary Data—Note 1—Description", "bbox": [143.8, 1274.1, 1072.3, 1294.9]}, {"text": "of Business and Accounting Policies”). Increased unit sales were driven largely by our continued efforts to", "bbox": [143.8, 1299.1, 1035.6, 1319.9]}, {"text": "reduce prices for our customers, including from our free shipping offers and Amazon Prime, by increased", "bbox": [143.8, 1324.1, 1025.6, 1344.9]}, {"text": "in-stock inventory availability and increased selection of product offerings, and by the impact of Zappos, which", "bbox": [143.8, 1349.1, 1076.9, 1369.9]}, {"text": "we acquired in the fourth quarter of 2009.", "bbox": [143.8, 1374.1, 492.8, 1395.0]}, {"text": "25", "bbox": [608.6, 1465.8, 629.4, 1486.6]}]}